questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue in a high-concurrency microservice. A developer implemented a recursive cache-loading mechanism using `ConcurrentHashMap` to handle hierarchical data. Below is the simplified code snippet: 

java
public class HierarchicalCache {
    private final Map<String, String> cache = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

    public String getEntry(String key) {
        return cache.computeIfAbsent(key, k -> {
            if (k.contains(":child")) {
                return getEntry(k.split(":")[0]); // Recursive call
            }
            return "Value_" + k;
        });
    }
}

During peak load, the service threads intermittently hang without throwing an `Exception` (on Java 8) or throw an `IllegalStateException` (on Java 9+).
